5:
Phew! Looks like these ruins are filled
with monsters after all.
8:
You should really conserve your
strength for the kraken we've been
asked to take down, but I don't know
if that'sâ€”
15:
Ha, you got me! I'm impressed. It
takes a lot of skill to sniff out yours
truly. Now you've got something to
brag about to your buddies back
home.
25:
Y-you don't recognize me?! What
kind of backwoods Float are you twoâ€”
28:
Hold on a minute. Those clothes...
Drifters, right?
31:
What's your business in these ruins?
Trying to make a living on bounties
or something?
36:
We received a request from a
nearby Float to take down a kraken
that has made these ruins its nest.
40: Oh... So you're monster hunting, eh?
43:
Then this meeting must be a
blessing from the sea goddess in
disguise! Mind if I join you on your
little adventure? At least till you beat
the kraken.
47:
I was just thinking I should really do
something about that nasty beast
anyway.
51:
Well... We would appreciate the
extra firepower.
55:
Then it's settled! Now, why don't you
two tell me about your home worlds
while we make our way to the final
boss?
60:
A World Flipper?! Now I've heard
everything! I thought you guys just
got stuck here like other drifters.
63:
But here you are, hopping around to
all sorts of different worlds!
67:
Yeah... I know it sounds like a fairy
tale, but that's our story. Do you
really believe us?
71:
Of course I do. You don't seem like
the type to lie. Besides, it's more fun
if I believe you.
75: Fun, huh? Yeah, I guess that's true.
80:
Just imagine all the worlds unseen!
Ruins unexplored! TREASURES for the
taking! There's no telling what kind
of thrillsâ€”
85:
Hold that thought! We'll have to
save this conversation for later!
90:
That's the kraken we're after! Get
ready, Alk, Marcus!
95:
Damn, there's too many of them!
Sorry about this, boys, but...
100: Hey! What are you doing, Marcus?!
122:
Sorry to leave that beast to you
without warning. You did a good job
pretending to panic.
126:
Well... All those tentacles were a
pain. If you needed a distraction so
you could aim at its vitals, who am I
to stop you?
130:
...Heh. You're more experienced in
combat than I thought.
134:
Still, you're a pretty good sport if you
can laugh about being made a
decoy!
137:
Don't get too soft though. You might
end up getting tricked by some
shady fellow! Be careful out there.
146:
I said we'd only work together until
the kraken was taken down, didn't I?
Kraken's gone, so I'm out!
151:
What a strange fellow. Going off of
his moves, he seems quite skilled,
but you don't feel particularly
guarded around him...
154:
Yeah, we were even talking about
the World Flipper with him.
158:
Anyway, let's go report back to our
contact. I'm sure they'll be happy to
know their Float is safe!
163:
You dirty rotten thieves! What did
you do with the treasure?!
169:
Don't play dumb! Our survey team
said the treasure protected by the
kraken has disappeared without a
trace!
173:
There was treasure there?! We left
as soon as we defeated the kraken!
177:
Hold on... Could it have been...
Marcus?
180:
Y-you two are in leagues with the
Thrill Seeker?! How dare you trick us!
183:
We didn't! If anything, we're the ones
whoâ€”
186:
You're the ones doing the tricking.
You used Alk and Light here to get
rid of your little kraken problem,
didn't you?
189:
As for the treasure, that's right! I,
Marcus, the great treasure hunter,
am its new keeper!
196:
H-hold it right there, Marcus! You
five, after them!
202:
Phew, that was a close one... Marcus
really was famous around here.
205:
More like infamous. What exactly did
he do to garner such a reputation?
209:
Nothing major. Just taking out
business rivals with traps in the ruins
or picking fights with pirates.
214:
Ahaha... Well, I guess we should still
thank you for the save back there.
218:
Ha! You really are a good sport! You
know, if I hadn't stolen that treasure,
those jerks wouldn't have
threatened you.
221:
Yeah, but you came to save us,
right? You didn't have to do that, but
you did, and that's what matters.
225:
Jeez, don't look at me with those
innocent eyes. I'm glad you
understand, though.
228: ...Hey, mind taking me with you two?
232:
Wow... So you really do believe our
story about the World Flipper.
237:
I see no problem. Welcome aboard,
Marcus.
241:
But in return, you'll have to help us
out on our adventures, got it?
246:
Damn, and here I thought I was
getting a free ride... That's fine by
me, but I wasn't expecting that from
you softies.
249:
Well, if we're too soft, we'll get tricked
by some shady fellow, right?
254:
Ha! Right you are! All right, consider
my interest piqued! Let's go!
